					<p class="content offset fade-in-400">
						At the turn of the century, the Santa Monica Bay hosted over 
						40,000 acres of kelp forest, and the diverse sea life that it supported.
					</p>
					
					<p class="content offset fade-in-800">
						During this time, the demand for sea otter pelts brought them to near elimination.
					</p>
